{
  "texts": [
    "Most data on political participation come from self-reports on surveys and voter registration databases.",
    "Civic knowledge and skills are a set of understandings and abilities widely viewed as conducive to self-government.",
    "Specific indicators include scores on factual quizzes regarding the country's constitutional system (e.g., Ten Dam et al., 2020), such as its separate branches of government, federalism, and how a bill becomes a law.",
    "Other indicators include self-reports regarding a person's ability to write a persuasive letter or give a public speech.",
    "Civic knowledge also includes \"understanding of and commitment to democratic norms\" such as accepting the results from fair elections even if they do not favor one's preferred candidate (Viteritti, 2001, p. 181)."
  ]
}